cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.CY, cs.CE 

This paper focuses on analyzing social media data, specifically Twitter, to understand advertising strategies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also heavily relies on natural language processing techniques to accurately gauge sentiment, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper analyzes multimedia content, such as images and videos, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also touches on the ethical considerations of advertising on social media, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of advertising on brand reputation, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
